<!-------- FAQ -------->
<section class="pmp-faq">
  <div class="media">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  </div>
  <a class="blue" href="https://support.ring.com/hc/en-us/sections/360002557451-General-Doorbell-FAQs" target="_blank">Still Have Questions?</a>
  <div class="media">
      <div class="pmp-expand">
        <div class="expander" onclick="expandFaq(this);">
            <span class="faq">What are the differences between Video Doorbell, Video Doorbell 3, Video Doorbell 3 Plus, Peephole Cam, Video Doorbell Pro, Video Doorbell Elite?</span>
            <svg width="33px" height="21px" viewbox="0 0 33 21" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
              <g id="Page-1" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd" fill-opacity="1">
                  <g id="RPP-Strikethrough-375px-Mobile-Default" transform="translate(-318.000000, -610.000000)" fill="#9B9B9B">
                    <g id="Card-Basic" transform="translate(0.000000, 586.000000)">
                        <polygon id="Icon-Chevron-Plus" transform="translate(334.500000, 34.500000) rotate(90.000000) translate(-334.500000, -34.500000) " points="324 21.3 327.5 18 345 34.5 327.5 51 324 47.7 337.890625 34.5"></polygon>
                    </g>
                  </g>
              </g>
            </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="expand" style="display: none;">
          
          <p>All Ring Video Doorbells can send notifications to your phone, tablet and PC when anyone presses your doorbell or triggers the built-in motion sensors. When you answer the notification, you can see, hear and speak to visitors from anywhere. The main differences between each doorbell are their additional features and how they receive power.</p>
          <p>Video Doorbell is powered by a rechargeable, built-in battery or can be hardwired to an existing doorbell system and works on any home. It features 1080p HD video and adjustable motion zones that let you fine-tune the sensitivity of your motion sensors.</p>
          <p>Video Doorbell 3 is powered by a removable, rechargeable, quick-release battery pack for easier charging or can be hardwired to an existing doorbell system and works on any home. It has all the features of Ring Video Doorbell plus 2.4GHz and 5GHz dual-band wifi (vs 2.4GHz only on Video Doorbell) for enhanced connectivity and an additional “near” motion zone that provides motion detection in areas only 5’-15’ in front of your home (reducing irrelevant Motion Notifications further away). Video Doorbell 3 also has improved screw strength, a redesigned easy-to-remove faceplate, and automatic chime connection which makes installing your video doorbell easier than ever.
          </p>
          <p>Video Doorbell 3 Plus is powered by a removable, rechargeable, quick-release battery pack for easier charging or can be hardwired to an existing doorbell system and works on any home. It has all the features of Ring Video Doorbell 3 plus our Pre-Roll technology, which allows you to see an additional 4 seconds of video before the motion event was even triggered – a first-to-market feature for battery-powered doorbells and unique exclusively to Ring. Pre-Roll video is in black and white and in low resolution to conserve your battery life. Pre-Roll works in well-illuminated areas. Low light conditions may affect the Pre-Roll functionalities.</p>
          <p>Video Doorbell Pro connects to existing doorbell wires for nonstop power. It features 1080p HD video, dual-band wifi, a slim design and customizable motion zones that let you create and adjust your own motion zones.</p>
          <p>Video Doorbell Elite uses Power Over Ethernet to connect to the internet and receive power. Ideal for new or remodeled homes, Video Doorbell Elite has a flush mount and a sleek design with customizable motion zones and 1080p HD video.</p>
          <p>Ring Peephole Cam is powered by a removable, rechargeable, quick-release battery pack. Unlike other doorbells, which are typically mounted to the side of a door, Peephole Cam can be mounted directly on your door to replace a compatible peephole. It also features 1080p HD video, knock detection, and adjustable motion zones.</p>
          

        </div>
        <hr />
      </div>

      <div class="pmp-expand">
        <div class="expander" onclick="expandFaq(this);">
          <span class="faq">Do Ring Video Doorbells save my videos and photos so I can review them later?</span>
            <svg width="33px" height="21px" viewbox="0 0 33 21" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
              <g id="Page-1" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd" fill-opacity="1">
                  <g id="RPP-Strikethrough-375px-Mobile-Default" transform="translate(-318.000000, -610.000000)" fill="#9B9B9B">
                    <g id="Card-Basic" transform="translate(0.000000, 586.000000)">
                        <polygon id="Icon-Chevron-Plus" transform="translate(334.500000, 34.500000) rotate(90.000000) translate(-334.500000, -34.500000) " points="324 21.3 327.5 18 345 34.5 327.5 51 324 47.7 337.890625 34.5"></polygon>
                    </g>
                  </g>
              </g>
            </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="expand" style="display: none;">
          <p>If you have a subscription to Ring Protect, videos captured by your doorbell will be saved to your Ring account for up to 30 or 60 days depending on your location, so you can review them at any time.</p>
          <p>Storage is for 30 days if your address is in one of the following countries:<br />
            Andorra, Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Republic of Cyprus, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Monaco, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, UK.</p>
          <p>Photos captured will be saved to your Ring account for up to 7 days. All Ring Video Doorbells come with a free 30-day trial of Ring Protect.<sup>1</sup> During or after a trial, you can choose to purchase a Ring Protect Plan to save your videos and photos.</p>
        </div>
        <hr />
      </div>

      <div class="pmp-expand">
        <div class="expander" onclick="expandFaq(this);">
            <span class="faq">Can I share my videos and photos with people?</span>
            <svg width="33px" height="21px" viewbox="0 0 33 21" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
              <g id="Page-1" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd" fill-opacity="1">
                  <g id="RPP-Strikethrough-375px-Mobile-Default" transform="translate(-318.000000, -610.000000)" fill="#9B9B9B">
                    <g id="Card-Basic" transform="translate(0.000000, 586.000000)">
                        <polygon id="Icon-Chevron-Plus" transform="translate(334.500000, 34.500000) rotate(90.000000) translate(-334.500000, -34.500000) " points="324 21.3 327.5 18 345 34.5 327.5 51 324 47.7 337.890625 34.5"></polygon>
                    </g>
                  </g>
              </g>
            </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="expand" style="display: none;">
          <p>Ring Protect Plans let you share your videos and photos with anyone, including neighbors, friends and family. All Ring Doorbells come with a free 30-day trial of the Ring Protect Plan.1 During or after a trial, you can choose to purchase a plan to save, review and share all your videos and photos captured by your doorbell.</p>
        </div>
        <hr />
      </div>

      <div class="pmp-expand">
        <div class="expander" onclick="expandFaq(this);">
            <span class="faq">What’s Ring Protect?</span>
            <svg width="33px" height="21px" viewbox="0 0 33 21" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
              <g id="Page-1" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd" fill-opacity="1">
                  <g id="RPP-Strikethrough-375px-Mobile-Default" transform="translate(-318.000000, -610.000000)" fill="#9B9B9B">
                    <g id="Card-Basic" transform="translate(0.000000, 586.000000)">
                        <polygon id="Icon-Chevron-Plus" transform="translate(334.500000, 34.500000) rotate(90.000000) translate(-334.500000, -34.500000) " points="324 21.3 327.5 18 345 34.5 327.5 51 324 47.7 337.890625 34.5"></polygon>
                    </g>
                  </g>
              </g>
            </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="expand" style="display: none;">
          <p>Ring Protect is a comprehensive service that activates video recording and photo capture, saving and sharing for your Video Doorbell 3, plus a few extra perks. There are two tiers of Ring Protect: Basic and Plus.</p>
          <p>Ring Protect Basic activates video recording and photo capture and sharing for individual Ring Video Doorbells and Security Cameras. It saves all your videos to your Ring account for up to 30 or 60 days depending on your location and photos for up to 7 days, so you can review what you missed and share what's important. Ring Protect Basic subscriptions start at only $3 a month per device. Ring Protect Basic only covers one device.</p>
          <p>Ring Protect Plus adds even more to your home security. It includes video recording, photo capture and sharing for unlimited Ring Video Doorbells and Cameras at your home, 24/7 professional monitoring<sup>5</sup> with cellular backup for Ring Alarm, and more. Ring Protect Plus subscriptions start at only $10 a month per location.</p>
          
            <p>Go <a href="/pages/protect-plans" target="_blank">here</a> to learn more about Ring Protect.</p>
          
        </div>
        <hr />
      </div>
  </div>
  <a class="blue mobile" href="https://support.ring.com/hc/en-us/sections/360002557451-General-Doorbell-FAQs" target="_blank">Still Have Questions?</a>
</section>
<script>
  const allExpandsFAQ = $('.expand, .grid_answer_block');
  let tick = true;
  function expandFaq(el) {
    if (!tick) return;
    tick = false;
    allExpandsFAQ.slideUp();
    $('.expander.on, .grid_question_block.on').removeClass('on');
    $(el).toggleClass('on');
    $(el).next().slideToggle(400, () => {tick = true;});
  }
</script>
